          "path": "/officials/governor-patricia-wells",
          "body": {
            "processed": "<p>Governor Patricia Wells has served as the 48th Governor of Columbia since January 2023. Prior to her election, she served as State Attorney General for eight years and was a federal prosecutor for a decade. Governor Wells has focused her administration on economic development, education reform, and environmental protection.</p><p>Under her leadership, Columbia has seen record job creation, expanded healthcare access, and significant investments in clean energy infrastructure.</p>",
